style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Previous outcomes included </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Royal Society of Chemistry: Planning for Success - Good Practice in University Science Departments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (2004)</span><a name="_ftnref19"></a><a href="#_ftn19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">When women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different employment sectors?</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Currently it is not possible to use HESA data to analyse</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">destinations of staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">leaving academia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> by gender</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. However</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">implementation of the Con</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cordat to Support the Career Development of Researchers has ensured </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">significant changes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to the HESA Staff Record</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. From 2012/13 academic year</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">data collections </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">will enable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">better analysis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">support </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">actions by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">institutions to understand the profile of the research staff cohort and track </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their mobility </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">between institutions and sectors.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst we do not currently have data on the transition of women specifically into non-academic careers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the What Do Researchers D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super"> </span><a name="_ftnref20"></a><a href