n style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">series </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">due in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">autumn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> 2013, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">analyse the data by gender.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">An </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STFC career path survey of former PhD students have found tha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t female respondents were as likely as male respondents to be working in a university environment 2 to 7 years after their funding ended.  However, women who had left academic research were more likely than men to be working in the public sector.</span><a name="_ftnref22"></a><a href="#_ftn22">[22]</a></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">RCUK are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a signatory to the Concordat to Support the Career Development of Researchers</span><a name="_ftnref23"></a><a href="#_ftn23">[23]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which also highlights the wide variety of career paths open to researchers and the need for the promotion of equality and diversity in all aspects of the recruitment and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">career management of researchers.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The BBSRC, MRC, NERC and STFC are also employers of researchers and they are working to improve the recruitment and retention of female employees. MRC, STFC, NERC and BBSRC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have developed a network of ‘equality champions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’ who have produced a cross-Research Council equality training programme and are raising the profile of the many activities through a regular quality and diversity newsletter. Additionally, BBSRC, MRC and NERC have developed an Athena SWAN network </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">suppo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rt </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">institutes through the pilot programme of the Athena SWAN award</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and STFC has achieved the UKRC’s SET Fair award.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">WISE</span><a name="_ftnref24"></a><a href="#_ftn24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">who promote female talent in STEM have recently published UK Statistics 2012 Women in Science, Technology, Engineering and M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">athematics: from Classroom to Boardroom which notes “only 13% of all STEM jobs in the UK are occupied by women. Fewer women in the workforce means STEM industries struggle to find women for senior roles or board appointments. It also means fewer women sett</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing up STEM businesses - which in turn limits the potential for economic growth.”</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What should universities and the higher education sector do to retain women graduates and PhD students in academic careers? Are there examples of good practice?</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he Concordat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to Support the Career Development of Researchers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sets out a vision of working practices, roles and responsibilities that the signatories believe will further the attractiveness and sustainability of research careers in the UK, and thus ensure the continue</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d provision of well-trained, talented and motivated researchers that is essential to the continuation of our research excellence. The Concordat signatories (RCUK, UUK, Funding Bodies and others) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are committed to the realisation of this vision in the UK.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e UK has adopted the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">European Commission’s 'HR Excellence in Research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">'</span><a name="_ftnref25"></a><a href="#_ftn25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">badge to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of effective implementation strategies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The award is currently held by 77 UK universities and institutions and 12 institutions have retained their award after</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a 2 year review.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Principle 6 of the Concordat: Diversity and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">quality must be promoted in all aspects of the recruitment and career management of researchers encourages employers to consider participation in schemes such as the Athena Swan Charter. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Three </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Year Review of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Implementation of the Concordat</span><a name="_ftnref26"></a><a href="#_ftn26">[26]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> noted “that the majority believe their institution is committed to equality and diversity and more institutions are signing up to the Athena SWAN Charter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rincipal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nvestigators </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">esearch </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">L</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eaders (PIRL</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> survey has been developed by the Research Concordat Strategy Group and the CROS (Careers in Research Online Survey) Steering group. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">PIRLS 2011</span><a name="_ftnref27"></a><a href="#_ftn27">[27]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> reports that women especially those in the 41 to 55 age group are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more likely to disagree that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">there was fair treatment in rel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tion to gender in the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r institution. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Individual HEIs and departments </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">encouraged to use the outputs from these surveys together with other surveys e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the ASSET survey</span><a name="_ftnref28"></a><a href="#_ftn28">[28]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and organisational staff surveys to inform </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">quality and diversity policies and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">activities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There are a number of examples of notable success which the Committee may wish to explore (e.g. Queens University Belfast was the first Institution to be awarded the Athena SWAN silver award and York Chemistry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> department was the first department to be awarded the Athena SWAN gold award.) A mixture of top down leadership </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and bottom</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> up activities is needed to drive the required culture change and this is why the emphasis in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">RCUK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">tatement of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">xpectations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Equality and Diversity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is for action at both the departmental and institutional level.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There are also a growing number of specific examples of Institution based initiatives to support for example returners from career breaks to re-establish their research careers, as well as mentoring support and leadership training aimed at women some of th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ese activities have been pump primed with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research Council </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">support</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Research Councils also provide financial support Daphne Jackson Trust Fellowships</span><a name="_ftnref29"></a><a href="#_ftn29">[29]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for returners to STEM.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In addition to sponsoring Daphne Jackson Trust Fellowships, STFC has a returne</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r category in the Ernest Rutherford Fellowship scheme.  Any Fellowships awarded to returner</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are in addition to the usual quota of 12 awarded annually and returner applicants are assessed on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the basis of their track record prior to their career break.  STF</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C also offer bursaries </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which provide support (up to £2500 towards the costs of, for example, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">additional childcare or other care and travel to the Host Institution or to meetings.) for those seeking to resume an academic research career to develop a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">proposal suitable for submission to the STFC Fellowship scheme.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Other Councils fellowships also encourage women applicants, part time awards and returners to research.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">MRC have a range of public engagement events promoting women in STEM such as the </span><a href="http://www.csc.mrc.ac.uk/PublicScience/FabricsOfLife/SuffrageScience/"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Suffrage Science</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> programme at our Clinical Sciences Centre and the </span><a href="http://www.centenary.mrc.ac.uk/events/mrcroyal-societywikimedia-uk-women-in-science-wikipedia-edit-a-thons/"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">MRC/Royal Society/Wikimedia UK Women in Science Wikipedia edit-a-thons</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as part of our Centenary.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research Environment element of the R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">esearch </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">xcellence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ramework</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> make</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">explicit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reference</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to the Concordat and require</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> institutions to ev</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">idence their support for the development of researchers and academic staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the submitting unit supports equalities and diversity.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The 'Every researcher counts'</span><a name="_ftnref30"></a><a href="#_ftn30">[30]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">resources</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to improve equality and diversity for research staff within the HE sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is funded by HEFCE with support from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the other HE funding bodies and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> delivered by Vitae.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This project </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">evelop</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a network of equality and diversity champions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">; produced</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> resources and case studies for staff developers to embed in training materi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">als for PIs and supervisors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">disseminate resources and case studies through national and regional events </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers? </span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Given the strong evidence of the need for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cultural change in relation to equality and diversity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">RCUK has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">publi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">shed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">tatement of Expectations for Equality and Diversity</span><a name="_ftnref31"></a><a href="#_ftn31">[31]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is statement follows from a major consultation with the HE sector about </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to influence those</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">receipt of our funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hrough it RCUK seeks </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to promote </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">further cultural change </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uncover </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">evidence as to how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">HEIs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are addressing these issues at institutional and departmental level.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The statement states that RCUK will review the overall effectiveness of the approach at a Depar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tmental / Institutional level through its Audit and Assurance Programme; discuss equality and diversity at Institutional visits; and reserve the right to introduce more formal accreditation requirements for grant funding should significant improvement not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be evidenced.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">RCUK are also reviewing the collection and publication of data to ensure that we can assess how effective our policies and procedures are in promoting equal opportunities, both as funders of research and as employers. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">RCUK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">participate in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> activities of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the Royal Society and the Royal Academy of Engineering</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> whose </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">diversity programmes, funded by BIS </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are improving the understanding of the scientific workforce, articulating the business case for diversity and sharing best practice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">www.rcuk.ac.uk.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.rcuk.ac.uk/documents/framework/RCDStrategylite.pdf</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.vitae.ac.uk/</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:Georgia; font-size:10pt">http://tisme-scienceandmaths.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/TISME-Participation-Report.pdf</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </sp